# Jenkins Failure Agent вҖ” Docker Setup

## Project Structure
```
jenkins-failure-agent/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ backend/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ agent.py
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ requirements.txt
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ Dockerfile.backend
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ .dockerignore
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ .env                  вҶҗ create from .env.example
в”ңв”Җв”Җ frontend/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ src/
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ pages/JenkinsAgent.jsx
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ Dockerfile.frontend
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ nginx.conf
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ .dockerignore
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ vite.config.js
в””в”Җв”Җ docker-compose.yml
```

## Quick Start

### 1. Set up your .env
```bash
cp .env.example backend/.env
# Edit backend/.env with your real values:
#   JENKINS_URL=http://host.docker.internal:8080   вҶҗ Jenkins on host machine
#   JENKINS_TOKEN=your_token
#   GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key
```

### 2. Build and start
```bash
docker-compose up --build
```

### 3. Open the UI
```
http://localhost:3000
```
Backend URL to enter in the UI connect screen: `http://localhost:8000`

---

## Commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `docker-compose up --build` | Build images and start |
| `docker-compose up -d` | Start in background |
| `docker-compose down` | Stop containers |
| `docker-compose logs -f backend` | Watch backend logs |
| `docker-compose logs -f frontend` | Watch frontend logs |
| `docker-compose restart backend` | Restart backend only |
| `docker-compose down -v` | Stop and wipe volumes |

## Jenkins on Host Machine

If Jenkins runs on your local machine (not in Docker), use:
```env
JENKINS_URL=http://host.docker.internal:8080
```
This is a Docker special hostname that resolves to your host machine.

## Ports

| Service | Port |
|---|---|
| Frontend (UI) | http://localhost:3000 |
| Backend (API) | http://localhost:8000 |
| Jenkins (host) | http://localhost:8080 |